```csharp
using Microsoft.Win32;
using System.Text;

public class RegistryReader
{
    internal static string ReadHklmSubTree(string path)
    {
        var stb = new StringBuilder();
        using (var rKey = Registry.LocalMachine.OpenSubKey(path, RegistryKeyPermissionCheck.ReadSubTree))
        {
            if (rKey == null)
            {
                return null;
            }
            string[] subKeys = rKey.GetSubKeyNames();
            foreach (var subKey in subKeys)
            {
                stb.Append(subKey).Append(", "); // Concatenate subkeys with a delimiter
            }
        }
        return stb.ToString().TrimEnd(' ', ','); // Remove trailing delimiter and spaces
    }
}
```

In the solution, the `ReadHklmSubTree` function opens the subkey at the specified path under `HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE` using `Registry.LocalMachine.OpenSubKey`. If the subkey exists, it retrieves its subkeys using `rKey.GetSubKeyNames()` and concatenates them into a single string using a `StringBuilder`. The function then returns the concatenated subkeys after removing any trailing delimiter and spaces. If the subkey does not exist, the function returns `null`.

